Detective services, GuardDuty, Macie, Inspector, and Detective.

Preventive controls block known threats, but you cannot anticipate everything that will go wrong. Detective controls watch for unusual behaviour after the fact. None of them block traffic; all of them surface findings for you, or for Security Hub, to act on.

GuardDuty is continuous threat detection. It reads CloudTrail logs, V-P-C Flow Logs, and D-N-S query logs, and optionally S3 data events, E-K-S audit logs, and E-B-S volumes for malware. Machine-learning models flag anomalies, unusual A-P-I calls, communication with known-bad I-Ps, crypto-mining patterns, and credential exfiltration. Enable it once at the Organisation level and it covers every account, and findings come out as EventBridge events so you can route them to S-N-S, Lambda, or Security Hub.

Macie is sensitive-data discovery in S3. It scans buckets for personally identifiable information, financial data, credentials, and health data, using both regex patterns and machine learning, and produces a per-bucket inventory of what sensitive data lives where, plus findings when something is exposed. Macie is the right answer for compliance audits over S3 data lakes.

Inspector is continuous vulnerability assessment for E-C-2 instances, container images in E-C-R, and Lambda functions. It scans for known C-V-Es in operating-system packages and libraries and for unintended network exposure, and it runs automatically on the resources it discovers, with findings flowing into Security Hub.

Detective is for incident investigation. It pulls in CloudTrail, V-P-C Flow Logs, and GuardDuty findings and stitches them into a graph linking principals, resources, I-P addresses, and time. When GuardDuty fires a finding, Detective is where you go to answer what else that principal touched, when, and from where, without hand-writing queries.

And sitting over all four is Security Hub, which aggregates findings from GuardDuty, Macie, Inspector, Detective, I-A-M Access Analyzer, Config, and third-party tools into one place, with C-I-S, P-C-I, and Foundational Security Best Practices compliance views. The cue map: unusual A-P-I or known-bad-I-P traffic is GuardDuty; sensitive data in S3 is Macie; vulnerability scanning E-C-2, E-C-R, or Lambda is Inspector; investigating after a finding is Detective; and aggregating everything with a compliance dashboard is Security Hub.
